<div id='processContain'>
	<div id='step1'>
		<div id='step1Img'></div>
		<div id='step1Story'>We first thoroughly wash every bean to ensure no outside factors affect the beans taste once roasted. This process is vital to the integrity of our taste</div>
	</div>
	<div id='step2'>
		<div id='step2Img'></div>
		<div id='step2Story'>Once the beans are washed, we roast them in small batches. The small batch technique was taught to our founder, Joseph, back in Heidelberg Germany. It is necessary to thoroughly roast all of the beans to maximize their flavor, while eliminating as much acidity as possible</div>
	</div>
	<div id='step3'>
		<div id='step3Img'></div>
		<div id='step3Story'>After roasting, we use a proprietary technology to fast-freeze the beans top make them easiery to grind. This allows us to pulverize the beans and create the most delicate of coffee grinds</div>
	</div>
	<div id='step4'>
		<div id='step4Img'></div>
		<div id='step4Story'>To brew the coffee, we take our freshly pulverized grinds and run them through our triple-trickle drip system. This allows us to maximize the flavor output of each bean while also eliminating any and all grinds in teh finished product</div>
	</div>

</div>

